# Fixtures are digest-pinned: their recorded sha256 must be what a stranger receives from a
# clone, on any platform. Git's autocrlf normalisation silently rewrites line endings on
# checkout, which changes the bytes and breaks the digest — verified by cloning fresh and
# finding a mismatch, not assumed.
#
# -text disables all line-ending conversion. Anything whose digest is recorded belongs here.
fixtures/** -text
